external_knowledge:
- Satisfaction refers to the average happiness score; 
- Economic prosperity indicates the average GDP per capita; 
- Areas represent the regions of countries.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS unique_sources_count
FROM (
  SELECT DISTINCT source FROM gdp_per_capita
  INTERSECT
  SELECT DISTINCT source FROM happiness_scores
) AS common_sources;

external_knowledge:
- 'ships' metaphorically represents countries;
- 'harbor' metaphorically represents the region (Asia);
- 'populous' here metaphorically means the count of countries in the region.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(country_id) AS country_count
FROM countries
WHERE region = 'Asia';

